{"uri":"oai:ojs.innovareacademics.in:article/377","url":"file:///opt/drinventor/epnoi-hoarder-1.0.9/publications/oaipmh/ijhs/2014-07-11/9b3b73c5-ed90-4939-b50b-c708008f7afe.pdf","source":{"name":"innovareacademics.in","uri":"http://www.epnoi.org/oaipmh/innovareacademics.in/journals/index.php/ijhs/oai","url":"http://innovareacademics.in/journals/index.php/ijhs/oai","protocol":"oaipmh"},"metainformation":{"title":"PHARMACOGNOSTICAL, PHYTOCHEMICAL ANALYSIS OF THE LEAVES OF PSIDIUM GUAJAVA LINN– ANAKAPALLI VARIEITY","published":"2014-07-11T15:56:36Z","format":"pdf","language":"eng","rights":"","description":"Objective: To explore the micro morphology and physio chemical parameters of the leaves of Psidium guajava Linn. (Myrtaceae) – Anakapalli variety.Methods: Macroscopy, microscopy, physicochemical analysis, preliminary phytochemical screening and other WHO recommended parameters for standardizations were performed.Results: Leaves (5-15cm × 4-6 cm) are dorsiventral, oblong – elliptic, dull grey to yellow green with entire margin, obtuse to bluntly acuminate apex and rounded to subcuneate base with short petiole. Microscopic evaluation revealed the presence of paracytic stomata, three layers of wide rectangular cells, circular secretary cavities, broadly bowl shaped vascular bundles, xylem vessels, phloem, and fibers.   Vein islet numbers, vein termination numbers, stomatal number, stomatal index and other physico chemical tests like ash values, loss on drying, extractive values were determined. Preliminary phytochemical screening showed the presence of sterols, tannins, proteins and aminoacids, flavonoids, volatile oil, terpenoids, saponin, carbohydrates and absence of alkaloids, mucilage, glycosides, fixed oil.Conclusion: Microscopic analysis was informative and provides useful information in the botanical identification, standardization for purity \u0026amp; quality and immense value in authentication of the leaf. ","creators":[{"uri":"http://resources.ressist.es/author/Venkatachalam-Karthikeyan","name":"Karthikeyan","surname":"Venkatachalam"},{"uri":"http://resources.ressist.es/author/THE%20TAMILNADU%20DR.MGR%20MEDICAL%20UNIVERSITY-CHENNAI","name":"CHENNAI","surname":"THE TAMILNADU DR.MGR MEDICAL UNIVERSITY"}]},"bagOfWords":["guajava","plant","psidium","medicin","extract","microscop","phytochem","studi","evalu","layer","number","analysi","physicochem","preliminari","screen","standard","stomat","solubl","compact","delhi","pharmacognost","method","shape","determin","powder","health","indian","pharmacognosi","presenc","caviti","xylem","phloem","glycosid","authent","scienc","lower","epidermi","pharmacol","anakap","india","morpholog","chemic","circular","broadli","tannin","identif","qualiti","materi","midrib","journal","small","figur","activ","research","periyanayagam","depart","madurai","paramet","microscopi","rectangular","vascular","bundl","index","volatil","absenc","inform","botan","report","variou","anatomi","charact","insolubl","palisad","thick","narrow","outer","crude","adulter","colleg","tamil","explor","varieti","other","oblong","ellipt","green","short","paracyt","stomata","three","secretari","vessel","islet","termin","sterol","protein","flavonoid","terpenoid","saponin","carbohydr","alkaloid","mucilag","analges","compound","ethyl","alcohol","institut","chennai","macroscop","observ","section","techniqu","tissu","water","innovar","white","fruit","through","follow","adaxi","lignifi","parenchyma","secretori","upper","matter","import","control","anonym","ojewol","south","aqueou","ethno","africa","ticzon","publish","effect","septemb","myrtacea","macroscopi","result","dorsiventr","yellow","entir","margin","obtus","bluntli","acumin","round","subcun","petiol","aminoacid","conclus","provid","puriti","avail","tradition","known","diseas","antifung","hepatoprotect","fresh","contain","quercetin","triterpenoid","guava","along","level","tradit","grade","collect","botani","jayaraman","director","tambaram","transvers","taken","descript","to